cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a layer-wise pruning method for deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed method in embedded systems, which suggests a potential focus on optimization and efficiency, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. Additionally, the paper conducts experiments on benchmark datasets related to computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), indicating that these categories are also relevant.
